1 No title is prefixed to this deed, and it is not numbered. It is, besides, written in a smaller hand, and with paler ink.

2 Aschetil FitzGospatric appears as 6 witness to No. CIV. (another charter by the author of the 0116 before us), besides being named in it as being the former tenant of the carucate of land thereby transferred to the Abbey. There can be no doubt that the said carueate is the land for which the eleven bovates here named were given. For, on that conclusion, the expression “propter iii bovatas terrae de in- cremento⁷’ is fully explained. As- chetil gave up eight bovates and receives eleven in exchange for them.
